path.aria-label:
This demonstrates, that we have the ability to create or use detailed to-scale images and svg's and place them on the map.
So it could be a farm layout, points of interest, paths and routes etc. Possibly even quadcopter photography.
The way I stuck this downloaded svg here, was that I took a screenshot of the visible part of this map around this point, recording the bounds of the view (the same bounds you zoomed to when clicking the fly-to button). Then I pasted that screenshot into a drawing program, along with the downloaded floorplan. Then I just arranged it to look like it does here.
